6:
Whew! Nothing hits like that fresh
ocean breeze, huh?
9: Indeed. It is rather strong, however.
12:
Aye. This ain't yer average transport
ship! She's a real speed demon,
lemme tell ya.
14:
Honestly, havin' you and yer crew
here is just a formality. Ain't no
pirates catchin' up to this baby.
16:
No need to apologize. We get paid
either way, right?
19:
That's surprisin'. I thought you
mercenary types loved to get
scrappy.
21:
Er... I dunno about that. Honestly, I'm
just happy to be out on the open
seas again.
27:
Only a technicality, of course! The
Crimson Blades actually—
38:
Finally... FINALLY! I've found that little
punk!
43:
"Forget the cargo?" What the hell are
they playin' at here?
45:
Uh-oh... This one might be on me,
actually.
49:
Spare me the details—full sail
ahead, men!
57:
Th-they might actually board the
ship at this rate. But taking the
head-on might actually be the
better option here...
62: Hmm... What SHOULD we do here?
66: In a spot of trouble, are you?
70: Huh? Who are you supposed to be?
75:
You may call me Cipher. I am a
witch—with the power to freeze time
and space!
84:
Ice cold, even. But thank you,
darling. Now then... allow me to take
care of this.
87:
The Ivory Reaper?! What's the
Scourge of the Seas doing here?!
90:
Cap'n! Our cannons be blocked!
And there's, uh... she's... it's...
91: It can't be... The Ice Queen!
93:
Don't just stand there and gawk, you
nitwits! Keep that hag away from
the ship!
98:
...Excuse me?
I don't think I like your tone. Ice
Coffin—bury them!
102:
I do hope you take the time... to
reflect on your behavior.
106:
That ought to take care of the
baddies.
110:
Now, now. No need to thank me all
at once.
114: Wh-what the hell have you done?
121:
You've frozen the damn sea! How
the hell am I supposed to get this
cargo delivered?!
126:
This shipment ain't ever gonna
make it at this rate! We had
insurance for pirates... but this?!
129:
Th-that's really outside my field of
expertise...
133:
S-so sorry! I, uh, I must get going
now!
141:
You don't need to pay us or
whatever, so, uh... good luck with
everything!
144:
...Why, oh why couldn't it just have
been pirates?
150: There you are! Why'd you run off?
155:
Y-you saw what happened there.
They were furious!
158: Yeah, well... You did freeze the ocean.
161:
I did what I had to—that ice would've
never melted if I'd stayed. Not only in
space, but time!
168:
Heh... I suppose you could put it that
way.
172:
Now that I think about it, there was
no reason for us to run in the first
place...
177:
I just can't help myself when I see a
soul in need, you know?
180:
She really went in there without
thinking, huh?
188:
Our meeting was no coincidence,
however. I'd... actually been
following you for some time.
195:
Is it true that you're associated with
the Crimson Blades?
198:
They were one of the most infamous
crews to ever sail these seas. One
day, they just... vanished. Since then,
rumors of their demise have begun
to spread.
200:
I had to discover the truth for myself.
Is it true that she's crossed to
another world?
207:
I KNEW it! Please, allow me to join!
This may come as a surprise to you,
but I'm quite keen to visit other
worlds myself.
212:
Huh. I mean, you seem like you
mean well. Just... try not to freeze
over our town, okay?
222:
Rejoice, friends. The one and only
Cipher, mistress of the ice, is now on
your side!
227: I don't know about this one, guys.
